        <h3 style="color:lightcoral;">Java JDBC Tutorial !!!</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Java JDBC is a java API to connect and execute query with the database. JDBC API uses jdbc drivers to connect with the database.</li>
            </ul>
        <h3 style="color:lightcoral;">Why use JDBC?</h3>
        <ul>
                <li>Before JDBC, ODBC API was the database API to connect and execute query with the database. But, ODBC API uses ODBC driver which is written in C language (i.e. platform dependent and unsecured). That is why Java has defined its own API (JDBC API) that uses JDBC drivers (written in Java language). jdbc drivers to connect with the database.</li>
            </ul>

